```python
df_voting = df_voting.set_index('congress')
del (df_voting['chamber'], df_voting['prob'])

#create unique list of names
CongressSessions = df_voting.index.unique()

#create a data frame dictionary to store your data frames
DataFrameDict = {elem : pd.DataFrame for elem in CongressSessions}

for key in DataFrameDict.keys():
    DataFrameDict[key] = df_voting[:][df_voting.index == key]


```


```python
X1, X2 = [], []
for key in DataFrameDict.keys():
    df = DataFrameDict[key].set_index('icpsr')
    df = df.pivot_table('cast_code', ['icpsr'], 'rollnumber')
    df = df.loc[df.isnull().mean(axis=1) < .25 ,:]
    df = df.fillna(0)

    x = df.to_numpy()
    x = StandardScaler().fit_transform(x)

    pca = PCA(n_components=2)
    principalComponents = pca.fit_transform(x)
    x1 = principalComponents[:,0]
    x2 = principalComponents[:,1]

    X1.append(x1)
    X2.append(x2)

    print('Explained variation per principal component: {}'.format(pca.explained_variance_ratio_))
    print('PCA holds '+str(round(100*np.sum(pca.explained_variance_ratio_),2))+
                              '% of the information. '+ str(round(100*(1-
                               np.sum(pca.explained_variance_ratio_)),2))+'% is lost')
```

```python
#%matplotlib notebook

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np; np.random.seed(1)

def interactive_plot(fig, ax, x1, x2, names, colors, parties):
    norm = plt.Normalize(1,4)
    #fig,ax = plt.subplots()
    sc = plt.scatter(x1, x2, s=50, color=colors);


    annot = ax.annotate("", xy=(0,0), xytext=(20,20),textcoords="offset points",
                        bbox=dict(boxstyle="round", fc="w"),
                        arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle="->"))
    annot.set_visible(False)

    def update_annot(ind):
        pos = sc.get_offsets()[ind["ind"][0]]
        annot.xy = pos
        #text = "{}, {}".format(" ".join(list(map(str,ind["ind"]))), 
        #                       " ".join([names[n] for n in ind["ind"]]))
        text = "{}".format(" ".join([names[n] + ' (' + parties[n]+')' for n in ind["ind"]]))
        annot.set_text(text)
        #annot.get_bbox_patch().set_facecolor(cmap(norm(c[ind["ind"][0]])))
        annot.get_bbox_patch().set_alpha(0.4)

    def hover(event):
        vis = annot.get_visible()
        if event.inaxes == ax:
            cont, ind = sc.contains(event)
            if cont:
                update_annot(ind)
                annot.set_visible(True)
                fig.canvas.draw_idle()
            else:
                if vis:
                    annot.set_visible(False)
                    fig.canvas.draw_idle()

    fig.canvas.mpl_connect("motion_notify_event", hover)
```

```python
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.animation as animation
from matplotlib.widgets import Button

X11, X22 = X1, X2

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
#fig.subplots_adjust(bottom=0.2)


#ax.scatter(X11[0], X22[0], s=10, color=colorArray[0])
#ax.set_title("Sample number: 0")

#interactive_plot(fig, ax, X11[0], X22[0], nameArray[0], colorArray[0], partyArray[0])

class Index:
    data = X11, X22
    data_min = 0
    data_max = len(X11)-1
    selected = 0

    def next(self, event):
        if self.selected >= self.data_max:
            self.selected = self.data_max
            #ax.set_title('Last Date Reached')
        else:
            self.selected += 1
            #fig.cla()
            interactive_plot(fig, ax, X11[self.selected], X22[self.selected],
                             nameArray[self.selected], colorArray[self.selected],
                             partyArray[self.selected])
            #ax.set_title("Sample number: %d" %self.selected)

    def prev(self, event):
        if self.selected <= self.data_min:
            self.selected = 0
            #ax.set_title('First Date Reached')
        else:  
            self.selected -= 1
            #fig.cla()
            interactive_plot(fig, ax, X11[self.selected], X22[self.selected],
                             nameArray[self.selected], colorArray[self.selected],
                             partyArray[self.selected])
            #ax.set_title("Sample number: %d" %self.selected)


callback = Index()

axprev = plt.axes([0.7, 0.05, 0.1, 0.075])
axnext = plt.axes([0.81, 0.05, 0.1, 0.075])

bnext = Button(axnext, '>')
bnext.on_clicked(callback.next)

bprev = Button(axprev, '<')
bprev.on_clicked(callback.prev)
```
